"The House had no opportunity to work and examine in detail the ddl Autonomia. The Chamber of Deputies has been reduced to the passage of majority agreements signed in the Senate. We are facing a serious precedent that we fear will be repeated shortly with the text on the premier that will arrive armored". So the Democratic Group leader in the chamber's constitutional affairs committee, Simona Bonafè, who added: "The government is radically altering the structure of democratic institutions and is doing so by imposing a real dictatorship of the majority: It is very serious, we are at a force never seen of democratic rules. Debates of the European Parliament the procedures with which the examination should impose an immediate stop of the work". &nbsp;
<h2> Hope, provision increasing inequality
"Today the House begins the general discussion on differentiated autonomy. It is a devastating measure that will spread Italy and dramatically increase in inequalities." He writes on social media the former Minister of Health and MP Pd, Roberto Speranza.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> Carfagna, contrasts the Constitution in various aspects</h2>
"We are in favour of differentiated autonomy, but it is realized in compliance with the Constitution. Instead, this provision, for the approach given by Minister Calderoli, contrasts with the constitutional dictate under different profiles." He said this in the Chamber Mara Carfagna, president of Action, speaking in general on the ddl for the implementation of the differentiated autonomy.<br> "Tanti - added - are the problematic profiles. The first concerns essential levels of performance: there is no guarantee that the Lep will be financed. And then, if you place the lept of the Lep upwards, the resources, given the clause of invariance of expenditure, you will be able to find only increasing taxes or cutting expenses. If, on the other hand, the asticella downwards, without the need to find new resources, will continue to apply the iniquitable criterion of distribution that is historical expenditure, with the crystallization of existing differences and the introduction of discrimination for residence. Another problematic profile, the total absence of equative and compensatory mechanisms. With the aggravating fact that a perequative fund was there, but the government almost zeroed it. In short, there is no financing of the Lep and there is no perequation, i.e. the two legs on which the differentiated autonomy should stand".
<br> "Even, predicting that they are transferable to regions 23 subjects means going towards a marked fragmentation of skills, then towards an increase in bureaucracy: Are we sure this is a business for citizens and businesses? Last two issues: the Parliament is reduced to mere notary of agreements between the central state and the regions, without any possibility to intervene or in the preliminary stage of preparation of the plan of understanding or in the next stage; the possibility for the regions requiring the differentiated autonomy of retaining part of the matured waste on the territory will result, says Banca d'Italia, a significant loss for the State of important budget items: how do you think to compensate for this loss? With shopping cuts? Increased taxes? Citizens - it has concluded - have the right to know".
<h2>Bonelli, Hall discusses after coups in committee
"After the events in the Constitutional Affairs Commission concerning the ddl on Differentiated Autonomy, it is clear that this majority has again stepped on democracy and parliamentary procedures. We are facing a real institutional coup that undermines the foundations of the legislative process. The constant forcings and obvious violations of normal bureaucratic iter are now a consolidated modus operandi. We are no longer talking about occasional "straps" but an attitude that makes all kinds of hearing and confrontation useless: an unacceptable situation". Thus, in a note, the MP of AVS Angelo Bonelli.<br> "In the Commission, a series of forcings have been implemented which prevented an adequate examination of the measure. This House was reduced to simple paperwork of the Senate, depriving Parliament of its essential role of discussion and analysis. The President of the House, Lorenzo Fontana, gave nothing to the examination of the measure in the Chamber, without taking into account the legitimate concerns of the oppositions, so this law arrived in court illegitimately. For these reasons, we ask for an immediate stop to the ddl, this majority must realize that democracy is not an option, but a necessity," he adds.&nbsp;
